Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => {
            // App losing focus (partially backgrounded)
        })
        .OnStop(activity => {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => {
            // App entered background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Or use the cross-platform approach** — override `CreateWindow` in `App.cs` and subscribe to `Window.Stopped`, which maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* runs on background for both platforms */ };
    return window;
}
```

**Key tips:**
- `Deactivated` maps to Android `OnPause` (partial background — e.g., notification shade)
- `Stopped` maps to Android `OnStop` / iOS `DidEnterBackground` (fully backgrounded)
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR/watchdog kills
- On Android, also handle `Destroying` — the back button can skip `Stopped`
